HEADWORD: Tethyodea
<hw>Te`thy*o"de*a</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n. pl.</pos> <ety>[NL.,
fr. <ets>Tethys</ets> + Gr. <grk>e'i^dos</grk> form.]</ety>
<fld>(Zool.)</fld> <def>A division of Tunicata including the common
attached ascidians, both simple and compound. Called also
<altname>Tethioidea</altname>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

